**Gratuity** is a one-time payment made by an employer to an employee at the time of resignation, retirement, or death/disability, if the employee has completed at least 5 years of continuous service. The formula under the Payment of Gratuity Act: Gratuity = (Last drawn Basic + DA) × 15/26 × Number of years of service. Gratuity is tax-free up to ₹20 lakh.
